defs.docs:
A wrapper around the procedural macro API of the compiler's [`proc_macro`]
 crate. This library serves two purposes:

defs.name: force
defs.docs:
Force use of proc-macro2's fallback implementation of the API for now, even
 if the compiler's implementation is available.

defs.name: unforce
defs.docs:
Resume using the compiler's implementation of the proc macro API if it is
 available.

defs.name: TokenStream
defs.docs: An abstract stream of tokens, or more concretely a sequence of token trees.

defs.name: LexError
defs.docs: Error returned from `TokenStream::from_str`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Returns an empty `TokenStream` containing no token trees.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Checks if this `TokenStream` is empty.

defs.name: Span
defs.docs: A region of source code, along with macro expansion information.

defs.name: call_site
defs.docs: The span of the invocation of the current procedural macro.

defs.name: resolved_at
defs.docs:
Creates a new span with the same line/column information as `self` but
 that resolves symbols as though it were at `other`.

defs.name: located_at
defs.docs:
Creates a new span with the same name resolution behavior as `self` but
 with the line/column information of `other`.

defs.name: unwrap
defs.docs: Convert `proc_macro2::Span` to `proc_macro::Span`.

defs.name: join
defs.docs: Create a new span encompassing `self` and `other`.

defs.name: Group
defs.docs: A token stream surrounded by bracket delimiters.

defs.name: Ident
defs.docs: An identifier.

defs.name: Punct
defs.docs: A single punctuation character (`+`, `,`, `$`, etc.).

defs.name: Literal
defs.docs: A literal character (`'a'`), string (`"hello"`), number (`2.3`), etc.

defs.name: TokenTree
defs.docs: A single token or a delimited sequence of token trees (e.g. `[1, (), ..]`).

defs.name: span
defs.docs:
Returns the span of this tree, delegating to the `span` method of
 the contained token or a delimited stream.

defs.name: set_span
defs.docs: Configures the span for *only this token*.

defs.name: Group
defs.docs: A delimited token stream.

defs.name: Delimiter
defs.docs: Describes how a sequence of token trees is delimited.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `Group` with the given delimiter and token stream.

defs.name: delimiter
defs.docs: Returns the delimiter of this `Group`

defs.name: stream
defs.docs: Returns the `TokenStream` of tokens that are delimited in this `Group`.

defs.name: span
defs.docs:
Returns the span for the delimiters of this token stream, spanning the
 entire `Group`.

defs.name: span_open
defs.docs: Returns the span pointing to the opening delimiter of this group.

defs.name: span_close
defs.docs: Returns the span pointing to the closing delimiter of this group.

defs.name: set_span
defs.docs:
Configures the span for this `Group`'s delimiters, but not its internal
 tokens.

defs.name: Punct
defs.docs: An `Punct` is an single punctuation character like `+`, `-` or `#`.

defs.name: Alone
defs.docs: E.g. `+` is `Alone` in `+ =`, `+ident` or `+()`.

defs.name: Joint
defs.docs: E.g. `+` is `Joint` in `+=` or `'` is `Joint` in `'#`.

defs.name: Spacing
defs.docs:
Whether an `Punct` is followed immediately by another `Punct` or followed by
 another token or whitespace.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `Punct` from the given character and spacing.

defs.name: as_char
defs.docs: Returns the value of this punctuation character as `char`.

defs.name: spacing
defs.docs:
Returns the spacing of this punctuation character, indicating whether
 it's immediately followed by another `Punct` in the token stream, so
 they can potentially be combined into a multicharacter operator
 (`Joint`), or it's followed by some other token or whitespace (`Alone`)
 so the operator has certainly ended.

defs.name: span
defs.docs: Returns the span for this punctuation character.

defs.name: set_span
defs.docs: Configure the span for this punctuation character.

defs.name: Ident
defs.docs: A word of Rust code, which may be a keyword or legal variable name.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates a new `Ident` with the given `string` as well as the specified
 `span`.

defs.name: span
defs.docs: Returns the span of this `Ident`.

defs.name: set_span
defs.docs:
Configures the span of this `Ident`, possibly changing its hygiene
 context.

defs.name: subspan
defs.docs:
Returns a `Span` that is a subset of `self.span()` containing only
 the source bytes in range `range`. Returns `None` if the would-be
 trimmed span is outside the bounds of `self`.
